<paragraph blockId="1.[941,1323,1021,1046]" box="[941,1323,1021,1046]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">
<heading allCaps="true" box="[941,1323,1021,1046]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" reason="1">
“ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="La Cepede" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[953,1311,1021,1045]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cynoglossidae" genus="Cynoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[953,1311,1021,1045]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">CYNOGLOSSUS BILINEATUS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="764" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1452,1085,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">
The fish referred to as “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="La Cepede" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[1057,1302,1087,1110]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cynoglossidae" genus="Cynoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[1057,1302,1087,1110]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Cynoglossus bilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” by authors is said to have been described by La Cepède (1802: 659, 663) as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="La Cepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[842,1036,1151,1174]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Achiridae" genus="Achirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[842,1036,1151,1174]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Achirus bilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is no indication that La Cepède had examined material. His account included references to: (1) “ 
<emphasis box="[867,1136,1215,1238]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bloch" authorityYear="1787" box="[867,1132,1215,1238]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pleuronectidae" genus="Pleuronectes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">Pleuronectes bilineatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Linné, édition de Gmelin”; (2) “Bloch, pl. 188”; (3) “Pleuronecte, sole à deux lignes. Bonnaterre, planches de l’Encyclopédie méthodique”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1452,1341,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">
Source (1) is 
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin, J" box="[968,1206,1341,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" pagination="1033 - 2224" refId="ref3361" refString="Gmelin, J. F., 1789. Caroli a Linne systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Beer, Lipsiae. vol. 1, pars 3: 1033 - 2224." type="journal article" year="1789">Gmelin (1789: 1235)</bibRefCitation>
. It explicitly refers to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bloch, M" box="[813,997,1373,1398]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" pagination="181 - 216" refId="ref3004" refString="Bloch, M. E., 1787. Naturgeschichte der Auslandischen Fische. Dritter Theil. Berlin. xii + 146 pp., pls. 181 - 216." type="book chapter" year="1787">Bloch (1787: 29</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 188). It includes no information not already appearing in Bloch’s text and therefore seems based exclusively on Bloch’s data. Moreover, it is not known that Gmelin had examined any material. Source (2) is plate 188 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bloch, M" box="[846,996,1501,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" pagination="181 - 216" refId="ref3004" refString="Bloch, M. E., 1787. Naturgeschichte der Auslandischen Fische. Dritter Theil. Berlin. xii + 146 pp., pls. 181 - 216." type="book chapter" year="1787">Bloch (1787)</bibRefCitation>
; there is no mention of the text. Source (3) is 
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnaterre" box="[880,1116,1534,1558]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" refId="ref3175" refString="Bonnaterre, [J. P.], 1788. Tableau encyclopedique et methodique des trois regne de la nature. Ichthyologie. Panckouke, Paris. lvi + 215 pp., 102 pls." type="book" year="1788">Bonnaterre (1788: 79</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 91 fig. 377). The figure is a black and white copy of Bloch’s figure. The description is that given by Bloch. There is also explicit reference to the French edition of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bloch, M" box="[1051,1241,1629,1654]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" pagination="181 - 216" refId="ref3035" refString="Bloch, M. E., 1788. Ichtyologie ou histoire naturelle, generale et particuliere des poissons. Sixieme partie. De La Garde, Berlin, Didot, Paris &amp; White, London. viii + 151 pp., pls. 181 - 216." type="book chapter" year="1788">Bloch (1788: 21)</bibRefCitation>
, but no mention of inner anatomy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1452,1725,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">
In conclusion, La Cepède’s account of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="La Cepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[1231,1426,1727,1750]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Achiridae" genus="Achirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[1231,1426,1727,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Achirus bilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based only on Bloch’s 
<emphasis box="[1063,1239,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">
Pleur. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="La Cepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[1134,1239,1759,1782]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Achiridae" genus="Achirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">bilineatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="La Cepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[1255,1451,1759,1782]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Achiridae" genus="Achirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1451,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Achirus bilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not, therefore, a new species but a new combination of 
<emphasis box="[844,1020,1823,1846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">
Pleur. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="La Cepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[915,1020,1823,1846]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Achiridae" genus="Achirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">bilineatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. As a result, the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="La Cepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[1277,1382,1823,1846]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Achiridae" genus="Achirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[1277,1382,1823,1846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">bilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not available for a species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1822" box="[1100,1235,1855,1878]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cynoglossidae" genus="Cynoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1100,1235,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Cynoglossus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Menon, A" box="[1251,1452,1853,1878]" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" pagination="1 - 129" refId="ref3584" refString="Menon, A. G. K., 1977. A systematic monograph of the tongue soles of the genus Cynoglossus Hamilton-Buchanan (Pisces: Cynoglossidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 238: 1 - 129, pls. 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1977">Menon (1977: 36)</bibRefCitation>
listed the synonyms of his “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="La Cepede" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[1103,1349,1887,1910]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cynoglossidae" genus="Cynoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[1103,1349,1887,1910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Cynoglossus bilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. Among these, the earliest available name for this species is 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker, 1851" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1851" class="Malacostraca" family="Plagusiidae" genus="Plagusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrilineata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Plagusia quadrilineata</emphasis>
Bleeker, 1851
</taxonomicName>
, thus the valid name of the species is 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bleeker, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[923,1400,1981,2006]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cynoglossidae" genus="Cynoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="quadrilineatus">
<emphasis box="[923,1222,1983,2006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="764">Cynoglossus quadrilineatus</emphasis>
(Bleeker, 1851)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
